UNITED STATES of America, Appellant, v. OREGON CITY WOOLEN MILLS, a Corporation, and C. L. Keily, Appellees. No. 11542. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. July 28, 1947. Henry L. Hess, U. S. Atty., and Victor E. Harr, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Portland, Or., for appellant. No appearance for appellee.

Before GARRECHT, MATHEWS, and HEALY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment of the District Court is reversed upon the authority of United States v. Palletz, 67 S.Ct. 1095, and United States v. Kromer, 67 S.Ct. 1095.
